<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n10138e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10138e">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10138e"> 138(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> caduceus</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Mercure <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> En qualit&eacute; de n&eacute;gociateur des dieux, il porte &agrave; la main le <mark>caduc&eacute;e</mark>, baguette magique ou divine, embl&egrave;me de la paix. Le caduc&eacute;e est entrelac&eacute; de deux serpents, de sorte que la partie sup&eacute;rieure forme un arc; il est de plus surmont&eacute; de deux ailerons. <font color="green">[In his role as negotiator for the gods, he bears in his hand the caduceus, the magic or divine rod, emblem of peace. The caduceus is interlaced with two serpents, so that the upper part forms an arc; moreover it is surmounted by two wingtips.]</font> <small> P. Commelin, <a name="NMGR" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#NMGR"><cite title="source">Nouvelle Mythologie</cite></a> (1907) 61</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
